
[1]whist

   WHIST, a. Silent; mute; still; not speaking; not making a noise.

   The winds with wonder whist, smoothly the waters kissd.

   [This adjective, like some others, always follows its noun. We never
   say, whist wind; but the wind is whist.]

   Whist is used for be silent. Whist, whist, that is, be silent or still.

     WHIST, n. A game at cards, so called because it requires silence or
           close attention. It is not in America pronounced whisk.
     __________________________________________________________________

